From 2048ca48b38699d492ccc361bfcee07727c73b90 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
Date: Thu, 7 May 2026 17:48:23 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] drm/bridge: sii902x: Convert to DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI framework
 with D3 Cold PM

Convert the SiI9022 HDMI bridge driver to use the modern DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI
and DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI_AUDIO framework and add D3 Cold power management
via DRM atomic callbacks.

- Set DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI | DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HDMI_AUDIO on the bridge.
- Implement hdmi_write_infoframe / hdmi_clear_infoframe with AVI and
  Audio infoframe handling. VSIF has no dedicated register space on
  SiI9022A TPI and is silently dropped.
- Add audio callbacks: hdmi_audio_startup, hdmi_audio_prepare,
  hdmi_audio_shutdown, hdmi_audio_mute_stream.
- Remove manually created hdmi-codec platform device; the framework
  creates it via drm_connector_hdmi_audio_init().
- Replace atomic_disable + mode_set + atomic_enable with a single
  atomic_enable. Output sequence: exit D3 -> set output mode -> D0 ->
  write video timing -> update infoframes -> start TMDS.
- D3 Cold entry in atomic_disable: save context, hardware reset, enable
  HPD-only interrupt, write D3 power state.
- D3 Cold exit in atomic_enable: detect d3_suspended flag, re-init TPI,
  restore interrupt mask and audio config register.
- IRQ handler: use drm_bridge_hpd_notify() exclusively; remove legacy
  drm_helper_hpd_irq_event() that left ELD unpopulated.
- Store next_bridge in struct sii902x (drm_bridge.next_bridge not
  available in 6.18); use of_drm_find_bridge() accordingly.

Tested on AM62P5-SK with HDMI display, HDMI audio, hotplug, and
suspend/resume with D3 Cold entry and exit.
